  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project will implement and evaluate a community-based intervention to improve individual
      outcomes in violence-related injuries and homicide. Young African American men participating
      in a focused deterrence program (the Birmingham Violence Reduction Initiative, BVRI) will be
      randomized to receive an additional individual intervention based on the cognitive-behavioral
      Reasoning and Rehabilitation program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
